# Naming Conventions

## Governance

Subordinate to `docs/architecture/ai-constitution.md` (priority 8). Consult `AGENTS.md` and `project-context` skill for project-wide conventions.

| Document | Path |
|----------|------|
| AI Constitution | `docs/architecture/ai-constitution.md` |
| Workflow | `.cursor/rules/workflow.mdc` |
| Universal agent instructions | `AGENTS.md` |
| Project context skill | `.claude/skills/project-context/SKILL.md` |

## Purpose

Provide consistent naming across the draft.io monorepo so code is predictable, searchable, and aligned with Clean Architecture layer semantics. Names communicate **role** (entity vs value object vs use case) and **scope** (module vs shared).

## Required Behavior

### Files & Directories

| Artifact | Pattern | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| Module folder | kebab-case singular | `players/`, `simulation/` |
| Entity | `{name}.entity.ts` | `player.entity.ts` |
| Value object | `{name}.vo.ts` | `player-id.vo.ts` |
| Domain error | `{module}.errors.ts` | `player.errors.ts` |
| Repository port | `{entity}.repository.ts` | `player.repository.ts` |
| Prisma repository | `prisma-{entity}.repository.ts` | `prisma-player.repository.ts` |
| Mapper (infra) | `{entity}.mapper.ts` | `player.mapper.ts` |
| Mapper (presentation) | `{entity}-response.mapper.ts` | `player-response.mapper.ts` |
| Use case | `{verb}-{entity}.use-case.ts` | `create-player.use-case.ts` |
| Command | `{verb}-{entity}.command.ts` | `create-player.command.ts` |
| Query | `{verb}-{entity}.query.ts` | `get-player-by-id.query.ts` |
| Controller | `{entities}.controller.ts` | `players.controller.ts` |
| DTO | `{action}-{entity}.dto.ts` | `create-player.dto.ts` |
| NestJS module | `{module}.module.ts` | `players.module.ts` |
| Unit test | `{source}.unit.test.ts` | `player.entity.unit.test.ts` |
| Integration test | `{scope}.integration.test.ts` | `players.repository.integration.test.ts` |
| E2E test | `{feature}.e2e.test.ts` | `players.e2e.test.ts` |

### TypeScript Classes & Interfaces

| Kind | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Entity | PascalCase singular | `Player`, `Team` |
| Value object | PascalCase descriptive | `PlayerId`, `OverallRating` |
| Use case | PascalCase verb-noun | `CreatePlayerUseCase` |
| Domain error | PascalCase ends with Error | `PlayerNotFoundError` |
| Repository port | PascalCase + Repository | `PlayerRepository` |
| DTO | PascalCase + Dto | `CreatePlayerDto` |
| Controller | PascalCase + Controller | `PlayersController` |
| Command/Query | PascalCase verb-noun | `CreatePlayerCommand` |

### Variables & Properties

- Private fields: `_camelCase` prefix (`_name`, `_overallRating`).
- Getters: no prefix (`get name()`).
- Booleans: `is`, `has`, `can` prefix (`isValid`, `hasStarted`).
- Collections: plural nouns (`playerIds`, `slots`).
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` (`ALL_PLAYER_POSITIONS`, `PLAYER_REPOSITORY`).

### Domain Error Codes

- Format: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` string on `readonly code`.
- Patterns: `INVALID_*`, `*_NOT_FOUND`, `CONFLICT_*`, `UNAUTHORIZED_*`, `FORBIDDEN_*`.
- Examples: `INVALID_PLAYER_ID`, `PLAYER_NOT_FOUND`, `TEAM_NOT_FOUND`.

### API & Database

| Layer | Convention | Example |
|-------|------------|---------|
| REST path | kebab-case plural | `/api/v1/players` |
| JSON field | camelCase | `displayName`, `overallRating` |
| DB column | snake_case | `display_name`, `overall_rating` |
| DB table | snake_case plural | `players`, `teams` |
| Prisma model | PascalCase singular | `Player` |
| Env vars | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE | `DATABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` |

### Packages

- Scoped: `@draft-io/{name}` (`@draft-io/backend`, `@draft-io/shared-types`).
- Workspace references in `package.json`: `"@draft-io/shared-types": "workspace:*"`.

### Injection Tokens

- Symbol with descriptive string: `Symbol('PLAYER_REPOSITORY')`.
- Export as `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` constant: `PLAYER_REPOSITORY`.

## Forbidden Patterns

- Abbreviations without domain meaning (`mgr`, `plr`, `tmp`).
- Hungarian notation (`strName`, `intRating`).
- Generic names (`data`, `info`, `manager`, `handler`, `util`) without context.
- Mixing singular/plural in REST paths (`/player` vs `/players` — always plural).
- camelCase database columns in Prisma schema (use `@map`).
- File names without layer suffix (`.entity.ts`, `.vo.ts`, `.use-case.ts`).
- `I` prefix on interfaces (`IPlayerRepository` — use `PlayerRepository`).
- Test files named `*.spec.ts` (use `*.unit.test.ts` / `*.e2e.test.ts`).

## Good Examples

```typescript
// File: domain/errors/player.errors.ts
export class PlayerNotFoundError extends DomainError {
  readonly code = 'PLAYER_NOT_FOUND';
}

// File: domain/repositories/player.repository.ts
export const PLAYER_REPOSITORY = Symbol('PLAYER_REPOSITORY');

// File: application/use-cases/create-player.use-case.ts
export class CreatePlayerUseCase {
  async execute(command: CreatePlayerCommand): Promise<Player> { ... }
}
```

```typescript
// API response field names (camelCase)
interface PlayerSummary {
  readonly id: string;
  readonly displayName: string;
  readonly overallRating: number;
}
```

```prisma
displayName String @map("display_name")
@@map("players")
```

## Bad Examples

```typescript
// BAD: vague file and class names
// File: player-stuff.ts
export class PlayerManager {
  async doThing(data: any) { ... }
}
```

```typescript
// BAD: inconsistent error code
export class PlayerNotFoundError extends DomainError {
  readonly code = 'not_found';  // should be PLAYER_NOT_FOUND
}
```

```typescript
// BAD: wrong file suffix
// File: player-id.ts (should be player-id.vo.ts)
export class PlayerId { ... }
```

## Checklist

- [ ] File name includes correct layer suffix (`.entity.ts`, `.vo.ts`, `.use-case.ts`)
- [ ] Class name matches file purpose and PascalCase convention
- [ ] Domain error `code` follows `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` patterns
- [ ] API JSON uses camelCase; Prisma maps to snake_case columns
- [ ] REST paths are kebab-case plural nouns
- [ ] Injection tokens use `Symbol('DESCRIPTIVE_NAME')`
- [ ] Private fields use `_` prefix; getters do not
- [ ] Test files use `.unit.test.ts`, `.integration.test.ts`, or `.e2e.test.ts`
